   Other Chemical/Physical Properties

     * Flaky crystals, white, crystalline granules, or a white powder. The
       drug is odorless, has a bitter taste, and is hygroscopic.
       Phenobarbital is very soluble in water, freely soluble in propylene
       glycol.
     * Bitter, slightly hygroscopic. Aqueous solutions are alkaline to
       litmus and phenolphthalein, pH about 9.3; 1 g dissolves in about 1
       mL water; 1 g dissolves in about 10 mL alcohol; insoluble in ether
       or chloroform /Phenobarbital sodium/
     * A 10% soln in water has a pH of 9.2 to 12 and slowly decomposes. A
       3.9% soln in water is iso-osmotic with serum. Loses not more than
       7% of its wt when dried. /Phenobarbital sodium/
